values: Most of you will know the sad story of how Sophie Lancaster and her boyfriend were beaten up in Bacup because of their appearance - Sophie died as a result of her injuries and her boyfriend will never fully recover from his injuries. The offenders were caught and imprisoned but their sentences seem light in comparison to what they did and the fact that they try to appeal against their sentences shows that they have no remorse. If you're not familiar, you can read about it here - Murder of Sophie Lancaster The Sophie Lancaster Foundation was set up to try and combat prejudices against, what is currently not illegal - prejudice based on individual's lifestyle choice - ie goth, metaller, emo whatever. Stamp Out Prejudice, Hatred & Intolerance Everywhere I know, many of you like me will have put up with a lifetime of verbal abuse from ignorant strangers, some of you may have been unfortunate enough to have been physically abused. Please help give this issue issue more focus and vote for the Sophie Lancaster Foundation to get funding for it's good work. Go to Have your say / http://cashback.cjsonline.gov.uk/cc.asp?area=20&mode=vote Scroll down to The Sophie Lancaster Foundation (4th from the bottom) and click once to open and then click again to tick. Then click the button that says "Have your say" That's all you have to do. Please - it only takes a minute! www.sophielancasterfoundation.com www.myspace.com/inmemoryofsophie Thank you so much! xmushx

Do not download anything called CommWarrior! I got sent a bluetooth message last Wednesday and thinking it was a game installed it on my mobile, I only noticed today that spam messages had been sent from my phone! It sends about 1 an hour and deletes the previous message. 

If you're unfortunate enough to get this on your phone you can get rid of it by putting:

http://mobile.f-secure.com/tools/f-commwarrior.sis
 in your mobile browser and follow the instructions.

Go to http://www.f-secure.com/v-descs/commwarrior_b.shtml for more info.

Hmm.

With a little tiny bit of salt but I've had to wait 40 minutes to heat it up in the microwave at work. The front of my thighs really ache, same as yesterday. No idea why. They feel like they are bruised all over. Listened to Zombina and the Skeletons on the Mark Radcliffe show last night. I miss listening to Mark Radcliffe-he makes me laugh lots! We went to their hotel as every pub in London was so packed as you'd expect. Think they don't hate me! We then went on th the Rock night at the Mean Fidler where we got in for free thanks to my mate David who was dressed up as a priest for the night and giving confessions and met up with Dean back from Wolvo days. Went to Pizza Express as Ross has been hankering to go there for ages and then we tried to catch the Corpse Bride but missed it and saw Domino instead as we didn't want to go home yet. What a pile of poo that was! Like what did we expect. Might go to White Heat thingy at Tatty Bogle tonight-it's Halloween and Comanechi are playing! Mark-if you want to come make sure you've signed up to their membership thing-won't stay too late though.

So I got the bottom set of my braces attached to my teeth yesterday. It's slightly uncomfortable. The most amazing thing is that it took me over an hour to eat 2 slices of toast this morning-longer with the first slice, then took a break and ate the 2nd slice with the aid of cutlery. I was planning on losing a bit of weight anyway so maybe this is a good thing. It's such a chore to eat!
Oh, tomorrow, Jaemi's band; Ophelia Torah are playing at the Colour Bar on Inverness Street in Camden and it's free! Everyone should come! Martin Gretch is playing drums, They have the current bassist from Queen Adreena, and of course Emma of Twist singss. It's gonna hurt me a bit but I'll just have to deal with it. See you tomorrow?

I have a peice of vindaloo brussel sprout stuck in my braces. Getting the bottom set on Friday, I don't like going to the orthodontist because he pulls my face around like he's struggling and angry.....

Joe Normal
34 % Nerd, 30% Geek, 17% Dork
For The Record:

A Nerd is someone who is passionate about learning/being smart/academia.
A Geek is someone who is passionate about some particular area or subject, often an obscure or difficult one.
A Dork is someone who has difficulty with common social expectations/interactions.
You scored less than half in all three, earning you the title of: Joe Normal.

This is not to say that you don't have some Nerd, Geek or Dork inside of you--we all do, and you can see the percentages you have right above. This is just to say that none of those qualities stand out so much as to define you. Sure, you enjoy an episode of Star Trek now and again, and yeah, you kinda enjoyed a few classes back in the day. And, once in a while, you stumble while walking down the street even though there was nothing there to cause you to trip. But, for the most part, you look and act fairly typically, and aren't much of an outcast.

I'd say there's a fair chance someone asked you to take this test. In any event, fairly normal.

Congratulations!

If you enjoyed this test, I would love the feedback!


Also, you might want to check out some of my other tests if you're interested in any of the following:

Buffy the Vampire Slayer

Professional Wrestling

Love & Sexuality

America/Politics

Thanks Again! -- THE NERD? GEEK? OR DORK? TEST



My test tracked 3 variables How you compared to other people your age and gender:
You scored higher than 12% on nerdiness
 You scored higher than 35% on geekosity
 You scored higher than 17% on dork points

Still can't run but I could last night after a few pints. Hmmm. I went to see my friends band - Veto Silver, they're kind of a bit like Sheep on Drugs sometimes and sometimes Apoptygma Bezerk. Then I really wanted to wee when Ross and I got to Camden to I we went to McDonalds (Oh dear, haven't for a long time, please remind me why we're not meant to go in there) and Ross bought some fries so that I could use their facilities guilt - free but there was a tramp in there or someone for a long time so after all that I had to hold until I got home. 
I'm very tired. Ross has gone to see his mate Lard in Watford. I might go home and try to buy some food with my chequebook. It shouldn't get cashed till payday? I only have half a lettuce, a tin of pilchards, wholewheat spaghetti and rice and 6 eggs, and some carrots and some houmous which should have been eaten by the 19th. I want pizza. I haven't had pizza for a while, but then my tummy is sticking out from my lack of running still since Saturday so I probably shouldn't. Maybe I'll practice MV songs. Theyr're really easy.
Fidel texted me last night. He wants to meet up later in the week. Says there is a lot to discuss. I thought it was over. I'm really not sure if I want to be involved with the Bone with all this childish crap.....

I am injured! After going out for Greg's birthday, Ross was giving me a piggy back and lost his balance. His knee hurts but I have ouchies on the inside and I can't run and I have to roll over and push myself up when I've been lying down. It hurts to sneeze and cough. It's kind of like where a hernia is but there's nothing sticking out (I saw a fat lady on telly with one once). Just internal pain......

So I missed the biggest party of all time because the celebrations fell on the same date as one of my brotehr's birthdays. He was 17 on Saturday. I felt sorry for him because no one else got him a card or a present, didn't do anything special for him. My dad took him to TK Maxx to buy him a No Fear t-shirt on the day and my mum bought him a cake but that was it. I told him he should come visit me before his weekends are swallowed by his part-time job. Poor kid, A-levels and then 16 hours at Marks and Spencer a week. Sucky. I was pretty bored and tired all weekend but then I needed to save money anyway as not much left on my overdraft after buying 3 Reading tickets (this year's and 2 for next year for Ross and I)
I still have 2 and a half weeks holiday left to take and considering how much I hate the cold, I should take them sooner rather than later. I usually sleep when I take days off-any better ideas?

Details Kick It Over 
HORDES

+ The View
+ Formula Bone 

Please be upstanding and welcome Kick It Over, our newest promoters. They'll be looking after the third Wednesday of the month,starting September, but we thought we'd let them get warmed up and bust some moves in August. 

Hordes fill the headline slot like '80s inspired neo-psychedelic revivalists mixing up The Cure, Psychedelic Furs and Syd Barrett. Winners of the Diesel Music Awards. We also hear Autolux and The Dandy Warhols, but from a distance, filtered through foliage. 

The View provide main support, dealing in Neil Young and Led Zeppelin slanted songs coupled with heavy bass and booty shaking grooves.

All this is backed by the incomparable [really, we've tried] Formula Bone. It's poppy lo-fi new wavish punk delivered with fire in the heart. Like The Monkees meeting The Ramones uptown after six Red Stripes and then some. But all you need to know is that they're enormous, inventive fun

So went to see NIN at Brixton Academy last night but I was totally pissed off that Trent Reznor's Stretch Armstrong appearance wasn't amusing me all night. Jaemi told me that he and Emma had decided that it wasn't a good idea for me to play in their band as I was too dedicated to Formula Bone. I was only meant to be filling in until they found someone but then Emma wanted me in the band but knew about Formula Bone. This was cool before. They haven't found a replacement. I've spent hours learning their music and gone to rehearsals. Why did Jaemi have to tell me on the day of NIN? Initially I said it was ok but I began to get more and more pissed off as the day progressed. This pissed me off so much, this was a really expensive gig for me since I bought Jaemi's ticket for him for his birthday and Sean's, just because he wanted to come too. I don't feel like speaking to him for a while, even though I know he's homeless (which is really his fault) and he's staying at mine.
Grrr.
Still, Pirate party tonight at the Underworld and Gig tomorrow at the New Cross Inn and then Sean's Dad's birthday on Friday and Godiva Festival on Saturday (anyone coming?) I must try and contact Lindaaaaaghhhhh. Sean's moving in on Sunday. Scary.

What's the catch though? It's at the New Cross Inn on New Cross Road. I don't expect anyone to come that far out to see us play but any support is appreciated! We're on at 9:45 possibly playing with Gemma Ray ( http://www.gemmaray.co.uk ) but not confirmed.

Fuckers.

Yay, Steve Lamacq played us on his show again last night! Again I missed it as I didn't tune in till 12am and then I fell asleep soon after. Not sure which song he played as it doesn't say on the track listing but I'm gonna root uot some earpieces to check at work tomorrow.
Been quite busy, Went to see Sean as he'd got me ticket to see Micah P. Hinson, strange baby faced skater guy with the wisdom and voice of almost Johnny Cash, a bit like Silver Jews style but not as tongue in cheek. He played with a band called Vetever and someone in this band's band befor Micah. All good. Saw Dinosaur Jr last week at the Forum, Lou Barlow was standing behind us! I kept my cool though. Saw Bobby Gillespie at the bar, he smiles in real life. Got very drunk after at the Underworld and then I cried when I got home. I used the lack of soup in my noodles as an excuse. 
I'm playing bass for Jaemi and Emma's band (Emma used to be in Twist) but I'm nervous about tonight. I think I need my distortion / overdrive peddle for courage. If Jaemi's nicked mu battery though, I'm gonna kick him.....

Went to see Patrick Duff with Kitten and Hazel at a special preview gig thing. I was never a Stragelove fan but he was really good! Ace songs, nice basslines, crazy man who aparently did acid with Keith Moon on harmonica.
I love shredded wheat.
Saw at a newspaper sign for Ham and High - "Highgate cemetery faces grave crisis"
Oh yeah, seen Sean and me in the latest Coco-Cola ad walking away from the camera in an underpass. I've fot a pink top and Sean's got a bag over his shoulder. The elusive man himself is aparently coming to visit me tomorrow for the weekend. I haven't seen my boyfriend for 7 weeks. It's a long time and I was starting to feel single again.....

3) I don't like it when people smell bad.

Been in MK since Thursday. I went to the orthodontist and they took x-rays. I knew the orthodontist assistant from when I used to work in Pizza Hut about 8 or 9 years ago-she's the smiliest person I've ever met. The braces are gonna cost a lot of money but atleast they'll split the costs over installments. 
Still practicing the new songs. I keep on playing the ones I can already play though-tut,tut. We're meant to be having a launch party in about a month so I've decided to maker some comic books for the promo packs. Gotta have these done by Tuesday though.
I watched make me a supermodel for the first time last night as I can't get Channel 5 where I live, only to see my mate get dropped from it. She's far more stunning than the rest anyway and I'm not being biased. 
Right, I'd better go and buy Easter eggs now!

Last night I went to see the amazing wonderful Queen Adreena last night! Katy-Jane was amazing. I got some great photos but they are on my phone. The support bands were Children of Fortune, I really liked them! and my mate's flatmate's band, Arial-X. Afterwards I went to White Heat and they played 3 Sonic Youth songs, 1 Sebadoh and 1 Pavement song amongst others-I was in heaven and also very drunk. I was very naughty and didn't get to bed until 5am thinking I'd be fine to get up in a couple of hours. I woke at 10:30am. Work were cool about it and I took the morning off as holiday. 
The weather's been gorgeous today! Sun mekes me smile (and causes aging of the skin)

I'm gonna be a roller girl tonight iving drinks out to people at my friend's club night. I only have roller blades though and I'm still not sure what to wear. I haven't skated for a couple of years though. Sure I'll be fine though.
I forgot my bus pass today because the beautiful weather made me take a different jacket. I decided to get the tube so I could leave at 8am instead of 7:40 to get to work.
